Judy Moores is a community volunteer and Davis Citizen of the Year in 1999. Judy has an A.B. degree from Mt. Holyoke College and graduate units from UC Davis in the fields of biology, education and human development. She has lived in Davis since 1966. Judy cofounded the Davis Science Center (Now Explorit), served on the Yolo County School Board, including two years as President, was on the board of STEAC, and has chaired the Sunday Services at the Unitarian Universalist Church of Davis.

